Original map: fy_snow_x by Skorz aka Punkii

This map was originally fy_snow_x by Skorz. He is my good friend. I designed fy_snow_2, fy_snow_3, and fy_snow_4 and made them with him back in the CS 1.3 days. He posted his fy_snow_x to FPSBanana two years ago. I made it into a GunGame map and added some new features such as the ladders to the upper area, extra walls for more cover in the open side areas, and elevated platforms to the sides as well as some crates, breakable boards up top, and snowmen. I also threw in some extra HE grenades and even some flashbangs.

Overall this map is very fun and very well made. I think everyone will enjoy it quite a bit. It deserves to be added to your server rotations on gungame servers.


COME PLAY IT ON MY SERVER:

WarmFuzzyLand -- 100 Tick | GunGame Turbo | FunSkins | FastDL
72.26.102.140:27015

I am back to mapping, took a long break, and am re-learning.  this is my first map since I started again.

This is a very small, close-range map I made for gun game in Counter-Strike: Source. The map is almost completely symmetrical, and includes: breakable vents, vent shafts, arched hallways, underground tunnel, bullet-proof windows (with ricochet sounds), and snow. This is my second map, and I like to think I'm getting better, so leave me some comments. This will make for a really fast gun-game round.

Just a small map I made while I had a headache and was really bored.
Its made with fast gameplay. I would recommend 10 players as a good amount but it can go up to 28 players. Although I don't think the gameplay would be good with that amount.

There is 2 maps - gg_sneak_day - It is not really light but it does not have the storm that could put you of and it does not have mist and that. It is a bit lighter but not too light. They are the first 2 screens. It does not have a nav file.
- gg_sneak - This is the storm version with mist and full detail. It is the last 4 screens and it has a nav to play on.

Hope you like it. Please post constructive feedback. 
Thanks; drimp.

Note: Sorry for the dx 7 screens. 
Also I think I forgot to put in buildcubemaps so if you get a shiny gun type it into console.
